18-1) Transivity Pairs : Describe the pictures using the dictionary forms of transitive and intransitive verbs :
  1) the door opens = doa ga aku
  2) you close the door = doa o shimeru
  3) the door closes = doa ga shimaru
  4) you put the dog in (the dog house) = inu o ireru
  5) the dog goes in (the dog house) = inu ga hairu
  6) you let the cat out = neko o dasu
  7) the cat goes out = neko ga deru
  8) you turn the light on = denki o tsukeru
  9) the light turns on = denki ga tsuku
  10) you put the candle out = rousoku o kesu
  11) the candle goes out = ouōsoku ga kieru
  12) you drop the pen = pen o otosu
  13) the pen falls = pen ga ochiru
  14) you break the toy = omocha o kowasu
  15) the toy breaks = omocha ga kowareru
  16) you dirty your clothes fuku o yogosu
  17) your clothes get dirty = fuku ga yogoreru
  18) you boil the water = oyu o wakasu
  19) the water boils = oyu ga waku
